    "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nCurrently, some methods in `policy.cpp` are inefficiently reallocating containers on each loop iteration. \r\n\r\nThis PR aims at optimizing policy verifications (transactions sanitization) by reducing redundant heap allocations without losing performance even in worst case scenarios.\r\n\r\n## Details\r\n\r\nI moved `std::vector` declarations outside the loop to reduce heap allocations.\r\nThis change allows the allocated memory to be reused between iterations and freed at function exit.\r\nSince std::vector only allocates on first use, there is no cost in cases where loops are not entered, ensuring zero overhead.\r\nI understand that most transactions only have a couple of inputs at most, so the loops will be executed once or twice most of the times, but this is a zero-cost optimization and still helps reduce the memory footprint for transactions with multiple inputs.\r\n\r\nWhile this could probably be detected by future compilers, my optimization currently shows around 7% improvement on existing benchmarks. \r\n\r\n## Benchmarks\r\n\r\n```shell\r\ntaskset -c 1 build/bin/bench_bitcoin --filter='(AssembleBlock|CCoinsCaching)' --min-time=30000\r\n```\r\n\r\n> before:\r\n\r\n|               ns/op |                op/s |    err% |     total | benchmark\r\n|--------------------:|--------------------:|--------:|----------:|:----------\r\n|          406,424.76 |            2,460.48 |    0.1% |     32.97 | `AssembleBlock`\r\n|              669.62 |        1,493,392.03 |    0.0% |     33.00 | `CCoinsCaching`\r\n\r\n> after:\r\n\r\n|               ns/op |                op/s |    err% |     total | benchmark\r\n|--------------------:|--------------------:|--------:|----------:|:----------\r\n|          407,556.77 |            2,453.65 |    0.2% |     32.96 | `AssembleBlock`\r\n|              618.29 |        1,617,365.94 |    0.0% |     33.00 | `CCoinsCaching`\r\n\r\ncompared to master:\r\n\r\n- `AssembleBlock` same\r\n- `CCoinsCaching` **+7.7%** faster",
