      "message": "optimize: reuse containers across iterations\n\nMove container declarations outside the loop to reduce heap allocations.\nThis change allows the allocated memory to be reused between iterations and freed at function exit.\nSince std::vector only allocates on first use, there is no cost in cases where loops are not entered, ensuring zero overhead.\n\nBenchmarks show a 7.7% performance improvement on CCoinsCaching.\nGiven the widespread use of policy validation across all transactions, the overall impact is likely larger.\n\ntaskset -c 1 build/bin/bench_bitcoin --filter='(AssembleBlock|CCoinsCaching)' --min-time=30000\n\nbefore:\n\n|               ns/op |                op/s |    err% |     total | benchmark\n|--------------------:|--------------------:|--------:|----------:|:----------\n|          406,424.76 |            2,460.48 |    0.1% |     32.97 | `AssembleBlock`\n|              669.62 |        1,493,392.03 |    0.0% |     33.00 | `CCoinsCaching`\n\nafter:\n\n|               ns/op |                op/s |    err% |     total | benchmark\n|--------------------:|--------------------:|--------:|----------:|:----------\n|          407,556.77 |            2,453.65 |    0.2% |     32.96 | `AssembleBlock`\n|              618.29 |        1,617,365.94 |    0.0% |     33.00 | `CCoinsCaching`",
